PN,46709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,FShe says more respite care should be
OL,7,Favailable to support parents. Respite
OL,8,Fcare provides short-term breaks for
OL,9,Fprimary caregivers of autistic
OL,10,Fchildren, allowing them time to rest,
OL,11,Fwork, attend appointments or spend
OL,12,Ftime with family, while also
OL,13,Fsupporting their mental health.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,FShe explained: "It's an opportunity
OL,7,Ffor parents perhaps to get to the GP,
OL,8,Fto work additional hours, to spend
OL,9,Fadditional time with the rest of the
OL,10,Ffamily, and it's preventative for
OL,11,Ftheir own mental health as well,
OL,12,Fbecause families are under a lot of
OL,13,Fstrain.
OL,15,F"They're having to fight continuously
OL,16,Ffor access to services, so respite
OL,17,Fgives them a breathing space that
OL,18,Fhelps to just keep them going. Respite
OL,19,Fkeeps families together."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,FShe said services often want to
OL,7,Fprovide respite but are unable to meet
OL,8,Fdemand.
OL,10,F"I'm aware of families where they've
OL,11,Frequested certain amounts of respite,"
OL,12,Fshe continued.
OL,14,F"The services want to give them that
OL,15,Frespite because they can see it's
OL,16,Fnecessary and needed but there just
OL,17,Fisn't enough places, staff, or money
OL,18,Favailable."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,FDr Williams also warned that while
OL,7,Frespite care requires investment,
OL,8,Ffailing to fund early support can lead
OL,9,Fto higher long-term costs.
OL,11,FShe added: "If we don't invest in
OL,12,Fearly intervention and good enough
OL,13,Fsupport, we incur costs long-term down
OL,14,Fthe line, so good support will prevent
OL,15,Fmental health difficulties,
OL,16,Fbehavioural difficulties and families
OL,17,Fnot being able to cope anymore."
OL,19,FA spokesperson for Gwynedd Council
OL,20,Fsaid that services across Wales for
OL,21,Fchildren with ALN are not enough.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,FThey explained: "Helping children and
OL,7,Fyoung people to have the best possible
OL,8,Fopportunities and to live their full
OL,9,Flives in their communities is vitally
OL,10,Fimportant to us.
OL,12,F"The needs of each child and their
OL,13,Ffamilies are unique and our care
OL,14,Fworkers give all their energy to try
OL,15,Fto ensure that we provide the best
OL,16,Fpossible support to meet the needs of
OL,17,Fchildren at all times.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G13/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,F"Despite the significant investment in
OL,7,Fservices in places like Gwynedd,
OL,8,FCouncils across the country continue
OL,9,Fto fail to meet the demand in this
OL,10,Fextremely important area.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G14/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46715
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,F"We cannot comment on individual
OL,7,Fchildren but we have seen an increase
OL,8,Fin demand year after year for support
OL,9,Ffor Autistic children or those with
OL,10,Fanother neurodevelopmental condition
OL,11,Fand the needs of these young people
OL,12,Fare increasingly complex and profound.
OL,13,FAcross schools in Gwynedd there are
OL,14,Fmore than 200 children with a formal
OL,15,Fdiagnosis of Autism and more than
OL,16,F1,000 children with neurodevelopmental
OL,17,For interaction difficulties."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G15/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46716
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,FGwynedd Council also outlined their
OL,7,Ffuture plan to increase their budget
OL,8,Fin social services for children with
OL,9,FALN.
OL,11,FThey said: "Alongside this increase in
OL,12,Fdemand, the shortage of carers and
OL,13,Fsocial workers is a major challenge
OL,14,Facross rural Wales, including here in
OL,15,FGwynedd.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G16/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46717
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,F"Despite the challenges, the welfare
OL,7,Fof disabled people and children and
OL,8,Ftheir families is most important. We
OL,9,Fappreciate how important temporary
OL,10,Fsupport is for families and sympathise
OL,11,Fwith parents who need more help.
OL,12,FGwynedd Council offers a range of
OL,13,Fopportunities for families of children
OL,14,Fwith conditions, including short
OL,15,Fbreaks in specialist accommodation and
OL,16,Fthere are plans underway to develop
OL,17,Fmore homes for children across the
OL,18,Fcounty.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G17/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46718
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,F"Gwynedd Council's investment in
OL,7,Fsocial services for children with
OL,8,Fneeds has more than doubled over the
OL,9,Fpast five years and we will increase
OL,10,Fthe budget again in 2026/27."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G18/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46719
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,FOn what it is doing to help support
OL,7,Fcouncils and families, the Welsh
OL,8,FGovernment said: "As a new Government
OL,9,Fwe will work with schools, local
OL,10,Fauthorities, parents and children to
OL,11,Fimprove the delivery of the ALN
OL,12,Fsystem, embed inclusive practice and
OL,13,Ftimely support for all children and
OL,14,Fyoung people. We have committed to
OL,15,Freview the Learner Travel Measure and
OL,16,Fassess ALN provision in Welsh medium
OL,17,Feducation, including the structure of
OL,18,Fcurrent support and training for
OL,19,Fteachers and school support staff.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G19/20
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46720
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1780506355
OL,3,CAutistic children lacking support as
OL,4,Ccouncils 'fail to meet demand'
OL,6,F"We are exploring ways to improve the
OL,7,Fintegration of education, health and
OL,8,Fsocial services to support children
OL,9,Fwith ALN, Autism, ADHD and other
OL,10,Fneurodivergent conditions. This
OL,11,Fincludes a person-centred and needs-
OL,12,Fled approach and ensuring lived
OL,13,Fexperience informs service development
OL,14,Fand delivery."
OL,16,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,17,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,18,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,19,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,20,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,21,Fbelow...
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G20/20
